Here are both approaches for passing data to `ProductDetailsPage` via Shell navigation, received through `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel.

---

**1. Register the route (AppShell.xaml.cs)**

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

---

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage (two approaches)**

```csharp
// APPROACH A — String query parameter (product ID only)
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// APPROACH B — Complex object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

---

**3. Receive data in the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, DB, etc.
        }

        // Approach B — complex object
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

---

**4. Wire the ViewModel to the page**

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

Register both in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();
```

---

**Key points:**

- **Approach A** (query string) is best when you only need a simple ID and will load data on the target page.
- **Approach B** (`ShellNavigationQueryParameters`) avoids re-fetching by passing the full object — no serialization needed.
- Both arrive in the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` method, so the ViewModel can handle either call site.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
